return(stats.skew(matrix),stats.kurtosis(matrix),plt.hist(matrix))

skew = 0
    kurtosis = 0

    for row in matrix:
        hist, bins = np.histogram(row, bins=3)
        # Calculate the estimated core density of the distribution
        cdf = stats.norm(np.mean(row), np.std(row)).cdf(bins[1:-1])
        core_density = np.trapz(hist, bins[1:-1])

        # Calculate the skewness and kurtosis of the distribution
        skew_val = stats.skew(row)
        kurtosis_val = stats.kurtosis(row)
        skew += skew_val * core_density
        kurtosis += kurtosis_val * core_density

    skew /= core_density
    kurtosis /= core_density

    # Create a histogram plot of the distribution
    ax = plt.plot(bins[1:-1], hist, color='red')
    return skew, kurtosis, ax
